SIMPLE: forefoot
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forefoot
<hw>Fore"foot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One of
the anterior feet of a quadruped or multiped; -- usually written
<asp>fore foot</asp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Shipbuilding)</fld> <def>A piece of timber which
terminates the keel at the fore end, connecting it with the lower end of
the stem.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forefront</ent>⟦br⟧
